&ldquo;WE ARE not just happy, we are celebrating! &ldquo;The community is relieved that this dog has died,&rdquo; said a resident of Crossroads, Nyanga, close to Cape Town.Lindokuhle &ldquo;Totozile&rdquo; Somdaka (24) was allegedly a legendary thug before he met his demise at the hands of those he robbed on Saturday morning.Totozile was beaten and stabbed to death by an angry group of residents after he was allegedly caught robbing someone&rsquo;s house.Residents repeatedly said they were happy the well-known thug is dead.&ldquo;This thug once shot me for my jacket,&rdquo; said a resident.&ldquo;He wanted to rob me, but I refused.&ldquo;That&rsquo;s when he tried to kill me. I went to the Eastern Cape to thank my ancestors after he tried to kill me and failed.&ldquo;We knew him, but police couldn&rsquo;t arrest him because he used strong muthi.&rdquo;Another resident said: &ldquo;We are sick and tired of thugs. What angers us is that most of them commit crimes and get away with it. Where will we live? We live in fear in our own homes!&rdquo; It is said the thug was caught breaking into someone house, then beaten before he was stabbed to death. The resident hopes that this will be a lesson to other thugs. Western Cape police spokesman Lieutenant- Colonel Andre Traut said: &ldquo;On Saturday at about 6.20am, a 24-year-old man was stabbed to death in Stulo Street by an unknown suspect who is yet to be arrested. The circumstances are being investigated. The motive is yet to be determined.&rdquo;